{
  "texts": [
    "Owing to the additional sparse restriction on the connection pattern, DH-SNNs do not increase storage and computational costs, allowing efficient execution on neuromorphic hardware.",
    "This work demonstrates a potential route to exploit biological observations appropriately for moving neuromorphic computing a big step toward real-world applications.",
    "The above metrics are easy options to select for measuring the performance of DH-SNNs, however, they are not intuitive for understanding the underlying working mechanism.",
    "To this end, we elaborate on a delayed spiking XOR problem as a simple but clear benchmark for the proposed DH-SNNs.",
    "In the naive delayed spiking XOR we demonstrate the long-term memory of each dendritic branch without state reset like the membrane potential."
  ]
}